'''Edgardo Issac Fariña Wynter''' (born 19 October 2001) is a Panamanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Pari Nizhny Novgorod|Pari Nizhny Novgorod]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Panama City]], Fariña represented [[Río Abajo F.C.|Río Abajo]] and [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]] before making his senior debut with [[Segunda División de Panamá|Segunda División]] side [[S.D. Atlético Nacional|Atlético Nacional]] in 2020. In August 2021, he moved to [[C.A. Independiente de La Chorrera|CAI]], where he would feature rarely.

On 12 July 2022, Fariña was loaned to [[Club Deportivo Universitario|Universitario]] for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol/lpf-cd-universitario-adquiere-dos-jugadores-el-clausura-2022-n5737982|title=LPF: CD Universitario adquiere dos jugadores para el Clausura 2022|trans-title=LPF: CD Universitario acquire two players for the 2022 Clausura|publisher=[[RPC Televisión]]|language=es|date=12 July 2022|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref> After featuring regularly, he moved abroad on 14 June 2023, joining Guatemalan side [[C.S.D. Municipal|Municipal]] also in a temporary deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publinews.gt/gt/deportes/2023/06/14/edgardo-farina-y-raul-calderon-se-suman-a-municipal-junio-2023.html|title=Panameño Edgardo Fariña y Raúl Calderón se suman a Municipal|trans-title=Panamanian Edgardo Fariña and Raúl Calderón join Municipal|publisher=Publinews|language=es|date=14 June 2023|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref>

On 31 July 2024, Fariña signed with [[FC Khimki|Khimki]] in the [[Russian Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Khimki|url=https://fckhimki.com/news/sezon-2024-2025/iyul/farinya-popolnil-ryady-krasno-chernykh/|title=Фаринья пополнил ряды красно-черных|date=31 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

On 24 July 2025, Fariña joined [[FC Pari Nizhny Novgorod|Pari Nizhny Novgorod]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Pari Nizhny Novgorod|url=https://fcnn.ru/news/38765|title=Эдгардо Фаринья – в "Пари НН"!|trans-title=Edgardo Fariña in Pari NN|date=24 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=ru}}</ref>

==International career==
After appearing with [[Panama national under-23 football team|Panama under-23s]] in the [[2022 Maurice Revello Tournament]], Fariña received his first call up with [[Panama national football team|the full side]] in March 2023, for a [[Exhibition match|friendly]] against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/marea-roja/seleccion-panama-vamos-la-ilusion-aportar-edgardo-farina-n5853839|title=Selección de Panamá: "Vamos con la ilusión de aportar", Edgardo Fariña|trans-title=Panama national team: "We go with the hopes of contributing", Edgardo Fariña|publisher=[[RPC Televisión]]|language=es|date=2 March 2023|accessdate=19 June 2024}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 12 March, starting in the 1–1 draw at the [[PayPal Park]] in [[San Jose, California]].

